(21999, 'FR_SI_1ICC3_.NET_LOREAL_IDF', 'LOREAL : Consultant junior Web/.NET pour la mise en place du wiki documentaire et de son alimentation initiale sur la solution SITECORE.\nLe consultant junior sera accompagné et supporté par un consultant Web/.NET/SiteCore expérimenté, basé à Sophia-Antipolis.\nLa prestation est à réaliser à Saint Ouen chez le Client.\nLa durée initiale est de 6 mois minimum à partir de début décembre, reconductible.', 'FR21839', 'BROUARD Francois S237718', '1970-01-01', '1970-01-01', ' - Products\nASP.NET-Medior', 'ICC', '', '', '3', '4'),
(22000, 'FR_SI_1SDM_SANOFI_Massy', 'Pour le client SANOFI, nous recherchons un Service Delivery Manager, pour développer les services chez le client et foisonner.\nSur la base d''un catalogue de Services, le SDM aura pour mission :\n- cadrer le besoin du client\n- le convertir en UO du catalogue\n- piloter et coordonner l''execution des services réalisés sur place ou à distance (équipe technique localisée à Sophia-Antipolis).\nIl rapportera à un Directeur de Projet.\nProfil : PM 4-5 ou BMC4-5', 'FR21839', 'BROUARD Francois S237718', '1970-01-01', '1970-01-01', '', 'PM ', '', '', '4', '5'),
(22006, 'AWL_UK_TfGM_1Lifevay_dvlp', 'Lifevay Developper.\nTo perform web based development associated with the SmarTIS product delivery for the TfGM programme.\nWork within a very high profile and dynamic programme. The team structure will also consist of distributed delivery teams primarily from Winnersh, Leeds and offshore (Mumbai, India).\nSkills\nEssential:\n. Strong Liferay portal development skills and experience\n. Familiarity with web design and coding experience (HTML, XHTML, CSS, Javascript)\n. Good verbal and written communication skills which will be used in order to cross skill other members of the development team in the nuances of the Liferay technologies\nDesired:\n. Good problem solving skills when dealing with application deployment in a Liferay context \nFamiliarity with XML technologies (XML, XSD, XSLT)\nUseful:\n. Familiarity with database technologies (MySQL)\nExperience in working directly with client representatives and being able to explain how the capabilities of Liferay can support their desires\nGeneral:\n. Must be comfortable working to an aggressive schedule and within a distributed and complex environment.\n. Capable, motivated self-starter with multi-discipline skill set and willingness to grow the core capability of the TfGM delivery team.\nOther:\nWill consider GCM 4 Java resource with strong Portlet development experience also, margin permitting.\nOccasional travel to Manchester possible to meet with programme management team.\nWhile the preference is to source a UK-based resource, consideration will be given to any suitable candidate from our global organisation i.e. remote and distributed working is supported on the TfGM account.', 'S235372', 'FASANO Fernando A407572', '1970-01-01', '1970-01-01', ' - Products\nXHTML, JAVASCRIPT-Medior, HTML-Medior, Liferay Portal-Medior, XML-Medior, XML Schema Definition Language ( XSD)', 'AD ', '', 'Leeds or Winnersh', '4', ''),
